
=Description=


"Community Networks (CN) are an emerging world-wide phenomenon that is receiving growing attention from a number of different disciplines. A CN is an infrastructure for digital communication, an alternative to the mainstream approach of commercial Internet Service Providers (ISPs). It resembles a scaled-down Internet and is used to interconnect a community of people who share particular goals and motivations."
(http://peerproduction.net/issues/issue-9-alternative-internets/peer-reviewed-papers/ninux-org/)

